The Proposal -
State to ecologically conserve lakes, rivulets and large water bodies in the state
The government launched the State Lake Conservation Scheme under the State Plan from the financial year 2006-07.
The plan typically includes the following:
1. To take measures to prevent pollution by identifying polluting sources of lake water.
2. Removal of necessary hazardous and organic silt accumulated in the lake.
3. To maintain the quality of the lake,
A. To control the growth of the lake by destroying unnecessary and harmful plants.
to take measures.
B. Improving the quality of lake water through biological processes in the lake.
C. Beach beautification, developing green belts, fencing, children's parks for recreation,
Boating, low-cost toilets, etc.
4.जनसहभ Programmes for awareness and prevention of pollution as per local conditions
